OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FMusic good for brain health
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fin later life - study      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Playing a musical instrument or singing
OL,6, could help keep the brain healthy in   
OL,7, older age, UK researchers suggest.     
OL,9,FPractising and reading music may help  
OL,10,Fsustain good memory and the ability to 
OL,11,Fsolve complex tasks, their study says. 
OL,13,FIn their report, published in the      
OL,14,FInternational Journal of Geriatric     
OL,15,FPsychiatry, they say music should be   
OL,16,Fconsidered as part of a lifestyle      
OL,17,Fapproach to maintain the brain.        
OL,19,FMore than 1,100 people aged over 40,   
OL,20,Fwith a mean age of 68, were studied.   
